&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Residential Support Workers&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bromsgrove Short Breaks Service provides specialist overnight and day care for children and young people with physical and learning disabilities across Worcestershire. Our standards are high and this is reflected in our home being rated as good by Ofsted.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have some fantastic opportunities happening in our expanding service&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a supportive and established team who really do make a difference to the lives of young people in Worcestershire. Worcestershire Children First recognises the importance of supporting, training and developing the staff who deliver services for children and young people.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Have you got experience in working with children or young people with disabilities, with a passion and motivation for doing to great job? If so, we would love you to join us as one of residential support workers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We require a number of Residential Support Workers at Grade 2/3 with part time hours varying from 20hrs -26hrs to compliment and help progress our plans.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Residential Support Worker you will be ambitious for young people, in helping them to achieve their goals and optimise their potential. You will work directly with children and young people, building effective relationship with them and their families and other professionals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Based in Bromsgrove, Worcestershire.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary from £20,903 (pro rata) up to £25,481 (pro rata) with additional payments through sleeping in.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Generous annual leave and pension scheme as well as a wealth of other benefits.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For more information contact Bev Harris Manager 01527 575710&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
